{
  "texts": [
    "Given the input context X, candidates Ẽ, and evidence for each candidate k ′, we prompt the LLMs to sample N reasoning paths where each path selects a single candidate that has the most faithful evidence and is relevant to X.",
    "We conduct majority voting over the collected N answers and select the answer that receives the most votes.",
    "Finally, the prediction is revised as ē = (s, t).",
    "The prompts used in our framework are provided in Appendix D.",
    "In this section, we design our experiments to answer the following research questions: Kang (2023), we measure the performance utilizing entity-level Precision (P), Recall (R), and F1."
  ]
}